CHATGPT MINI CHEAT SHEET
GUIDELINES
From the second I decided to create content around
ChatGPT it was clear to me that including the following
guidelines would be essential to get the most out of the fol-
lowing prompts, so read them carefully as one can easily get
lost in the conversational ﬂow ChatGPT provides.
Consider Privacy
Chatbots often collect and store personal data, so it's import-
ant to ensure that you only feed it data that you would also
share in a typical social media post.
Be Transparent
When you use the outputs in your everyday life it's import-
ant to be upfront about the fact that you are using a
chatbot. This helps with managing future expectations and
allows yourself to maintain your self-respect. For example, I
used ChatGPT extensively in the creation of this e-book, but
besides the legal text and some of the examples, none of it
was copy-pasted. See how this works? There is no shame
in using freely available technology to your advantage. Just
don't deceive others as this will always(!) catch up with you
in unpredictable ways.
3
CHATGPT MINI CHEAT SHEET
Plagiarism
AI detection software is being worked and improved on
every day. So don’t expect any of the blindly copy-pasted
chatbot outputs to stand the test of time. Especially when it
comes to critical pieces of work that you intend to build your
life upon (such as a university thesis or a book). As of 2023 the
best use-case for this technology is to kickstart your project
or idea, so don’t just blindly copy-paste without disclosing
the use of AI tools. Take what it gives you and expand it with
your own thoughts and ideas.
The Bias Is Real
Chatbots can often reﬂect the biases of their creators or the
data they are trained on. It's essential to be aware of these
biases and to use chatbots to improve and uplift your and
others actions.
Personal Responsibility
It should go without saying that chatbots are not a replace-
ment for human interaction and should not be used to
exploit or manipulate others. AI can give you some amaz-
ing abilities and powers, but it’s up to you to use them
responsibly.

Explainer
The focus of this mini-e-book is presenting you with prompts

and hit enter
■ Formula – Customize the prompts to your own needs.
Replace the word in square brackets with your very own.
■ Example – Get inspired by some practical use-cases that
are also copy-paste ready.

PRODUCTIVITY
GENERATE IDEAS
Prompt
Can you give me ideas for blog posts about real estate, per-
haps covering topics such as buying, selling, investing, or
managing property?
Formula
Can you give me ideas for [format] about [subject], perhaps
covering [topics]?
Examples
■ Can you give me ideas for a series of blog posts
about sustainability, perhaps covering topics like
eco-friendly fashion, zero waste living, and renew-
able energy?
■ Can you give me ideas for a webinar about ﬁtness,
perhaps covering topics like workout routines, nutri-
tion, and rest and recovery?
■ Can you give me ideas for a podcast about mental
health, perhaps covering topics like self-care, ther-
apy, and mindfulness?
